The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks (CNN) for high-resolution remote-sensing imagery retrieval (HRRSIR), which involves computer vision and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for feature extraction, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
